HEADWORD: Gymnoplast
<hw>Gym"no*plast</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧m"n⟦osl⟧*pl⟦acr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>gymno`s</grk> naked + <grk>pla`ssein</grk> to shape,
mold.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A cell or mass of protoplasm devoid
of an envelope, as a white blood corpuscle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

